      "hypothesis": "In stressed bear phases of a credit-sensitive financial, downside CUSUM impulses (cumulative 1-ATR moves) mark forced de-risking flow that persists for several bars: too much systematic supply to clear in one bar. The meta keeps events where credit spreads are widening (cs_spread_21 elevated) and real yields falling, dropping counter-regime bounces; expect many small wins with symmetric barriers rather than long asymmetric runs. cusum is event-based (no trend-archetype R:R bound) - the continuation claim is direction/timing, not payoff asymmetry.",
      "causal_story": "A balance-sheet-levered insurer is a short-duration credit instrument in equity form: when corporate spreads widen (cs_spread_21 med_q 0.645 here) and real yields fall (real_yield_5y_z252d 0.315), its funding discount is repriced by systematic de-risking flow (volume 0.704) too large to clear in one bar, producing short-horizon drift after 1-ATR CUSUM impulses. The primary is regime-correlated (impulses cluster in stress), so under add_feature the flag should earn MDA via interaction with cs_spread_21: credit widening only predicts continuation when the flag is on. Dominant-episode risk (39.8pct) guarded by the per-episode survival criterion across the 8 ordinals.",
      "feature_overrides": {
        "add": [
          "cs_spread_21",
          "real_yield_5y_z252d",
          "us_5y2y_z252",
          "volume",
          "vix_chg_5"
        ],
        "drop": []
      },
      "barrier_geometry_attestation": {
        "tp_atr_mult": 1.5,
        "sl_atr_mult": 1.5,
        "rationale": "Dossier baseline profile (hit_q 1.0, ret_q 0.25) shows many small wins; symmetric 1.5/1.5 is reachable within the pinned h10 horizon and matches flow-driven short drift rather than a long asymmetric trend run."
      },
      "falsification_criterion": {
